\begin_layout Standard
Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:rssFNBtoF3andFFC4"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 displays the residual sums of squares for PPR and LS fits to the weekly
 returns of FNB in 2008.
 PPR roughly halves the error variance, in part due to the fact that it
 fits the data with non-linear ridge functions.
 It is striking that both fits see little improvement when moving from three
 factors to four, supporting the widely-held view that equity returns are
 explained in large part by a few systematic factors.
\end_layout

